subject: Re: What does the |K| character mean
msgSnippet: I m not sure what this is.  My guess is that it s either a form of H with the end curled up to connect to the next letter or it s a ligature of H@ (= Ht .
messageBody:
I'm not sure what this is. My guess is that it's either a form of \H\ with the end
curled up to connect to the next letter or it's a ligature of \H@\ (= \Ht\. It's not a
common cluster, though.

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "BP Jonsson" <bpj@m...> wrote:
>
> What does the character mapped to the capital |K| key
> in the fonts mean? I guess it is _shw_ or _sht_, but
> I can't find it in the manual...
>
> TIA,
> --
>
> /BP 8^)>

> (Tacitus)
